title: Fifth-order Korteweg–De Vries equation
summary: A fifth-order Korteweg–De Vries (KdV) equation is a nonlinear partial differential equation in 1+1 dimensions related to the Korteweg–De Vries equation.[1] Fifth order KdV equations may be used to model dispersive phenomena such as plasma waves when the third-order contributions are small.
